{
  // Declaration-only build config. The package `build` script runs tsup for the
  // JS bundle and then `tsc -p tsconfig.build.json` for the .d.ts files.
  //
  // Why a dedicated config (declaration emit): tsup's `dts: true` path
  // (rollup-plugin-dts) drives the TypeScript compiler API programmatically,
  // which is unreliable on the TS7.0 GA native compiler (the stable programmatic
  // API lands in 7.1) — and the rest of the workspace targets TS7. The native
  // `tsc --emitDeclarationOnly` CLI emits declarations correctly, so
  // declarations are generated here instead of via tsup.
  //
  // `include` is narrowed to just the two public entry points; tsc transitively
  // pulls in every real src file they import, but *.test.ts / scripts / root
  // *.config.ts stay out of the program, so no stray declaration files leak
  // into dist/. `rootDir` is set explicitly to keep dist/ mirroring src/ (and
  // TS7 requires it when outDir is set — error TS5011).
  //
  // Why this package pins typescript to "6.0.3" (TS6) while the workspace is on
  // TS7 (see package.json devDependencies): the SDK's OpenAPI codegen,
  // @hey-api/openapi-ts@0.64, is not TS7-compatible (peer dep typescript
  // ^5.5.3; it consumes the TS programmatic API and crashes on TS7 with
  // "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'LineFeed')"). That breaks the
  // `generate` script and src/runtime-config.test.ts (which imports
  // openapi-ts.config.ts) under TS7. pnpm scopes this pin to packages/sdk only —
  // apps/tanstack-min and future members stay on TS7 via tsconfig.base.json.
  // When @hey-api/openapi-ts ships TS7 support, bump this devDep to "^7" and the
  // native-tsc declaration path above already works unchanged.
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "declaration": true,
    "emitDeclarationOnly": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "include": ["src/index.ts", "src/server/index.ts"],
  "exclude": ["**/*.test.ts", "scripts", "**/*.config.ts"]
}
